26/10/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- Police on Friday (October 24th) found 45 illegal immigrants enduring squalid conditions in Athens' western suburbs. 
Most of the immigrants, from Pakistan, Bangladesh, Myanmar and Somalia, were kept in a shanty and were being required to pay 7,000 euros each for their release. 
One arrest has been made and three other people are being sought for trafficking.
In other news, the driver of a truck containing illegal immigrants escaped from police who spotted the vehicle on the Egnatia highway. 
About 40 migrants were found in the vehicle. 
The driver pulled over and ran away after he noticed police chasing him. 
(ANA-MPA, MIA - 24/10/08)
